<div id="content"> <font color="#198a8a"><font style="font-size: 25pt;" size="6"><span style="background: transparent none repeat scroll 0% 50%; -moz-background-clip: border; -moz-background-origin: padding; -moz-background-inline-policy: continuous;"><big><big><span style="color: rgb(153, 153, 153);" /></big></big></span></font></font><font color="#198a8a"><font style="font-size: 25pt;" size="6"><span style="background: transparent none repeat scroll 0% 50%; -moz-background-clip: border; -moz-background-origin: padding; -moz-background-inline-policy: continuous;"><big><big><span style="color: rgb(153, 153, 153);"><img style="width: 270px; height: 60px;" alt="" src="1ant.jpg" align="middle" /></span></big></big></span></font></font><span style="font-weight: bold;"><br />
ANT.1D</span>
makes use of a
pre-computed Hamiltonian for the scattering section
and for the disorder-free regions. It
can thus be
used with tight-binding parametrized models or as a post-processing
procedure to a one-dimensional periodic
boundary conditions
self-consistent
electronic structure calculation using, e.g., CRYSTAL or SIESTA codes.<br />
<div style="text-align: center;"><img style="width: 324px; height: 239px;" alt="" src="images/supercell.jpg" class="thumbnail" /><br />
</div>
<strong><br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Basic
functionality:<br />
</strong>
<ul>
  <li>Spin-resolved coherent transmission
spectrum and
eigenchannel
transmissions.</li>
  <li><br />
  </li>
  <li>Density of states
and projected
density of states on selected
atomic orbitals.</li>
  <li><br />
  </li>
  <li>Charge and spin
Mulliken population analysis. </li>
  <br />
  <strong>Additional features:</strong><br />
</ul>
Interface for extracting the necessary Hamiltonians from CRYSTAL
calculations.<br />
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold;">Advanced features:</span><br />
Correlated
electronic transmission function
taking into
account
electronic interaction self-energy.<br />
<ul>
  <li> <correlated electronic="" transmission="" function="" taking="" into="" account="" electron-interaction="" self-energy=""><br />
    </correlated></li>
  <li><correlated electronic="" transmission="" function="" taking="" into="" account="" electron-interaction="" self-energy="">Interface
to NCA and OCA impurity solvers for calculating electronic
self-energy.</correlated></li>
  <li><br />
  </li>
  <li>Dynamical Mean-Field Theory for nanoscopic
conductors.</li>
</ul>
</div>
